### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  ClinicFlow API – Endpoint Test Suite
###  Open in VS Code with the REST Client extension (Ctrl+Shift+P → "REST Client")
###  Run requests top-to-bottom; after each POST, paste the returned ID into
###  the matching variable below so dependent requests resolve correctly.
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@host = http://localhost:5032

# ── Paste IDs here after running the corresponding POST ──────────────────────
@userId        = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@clinicId      = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@patientId     = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@providerId    = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@appointmentId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@waitlistId    = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@roomId        = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
@encounterId   = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  1. USERS  –  /Users
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1-A  GET all users
GET {{host}}/Users
Accept: application/json

###

### 1-B  POST create user  →  copy UserID into @userId above
POST {{host}}/Users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Dr. Alice Sharma",
  "role": "Clinician",
  "email": "alice.sharma@clinicflow.com",
  "password": "SecurePass1",
  "phone": "555-0101"
}

###

### 1-C  GET single user
GET {{host}}/Users/{{userId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 1-D  PUT update user
PUT {{host}}/Users/{{userId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Dr. Alice Sharma-Patel",
  "email": "alice.sharma@clinicflow.com",
  "phone": "555-0199",
  "status": "Active"
}

###

### 1-E  POST validation error – missing required fields
POST {{host}}/Users
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "",
  "role": "InvalidRole",
  "email": "bad-email",
  "password": "123"
}

###

### 1-F  DELETE user  (run last in this section)
DELETE {{host}}/Users/{{userId}}

###


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  2. CLINICS  –  /Clinics
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2-A  GET all clinics
GET {{host}}/Clinics
Accept: application/json

###

### 2-B  POST create clinic  →  copy ClinicID into @clinicId above
POST {{host}}/Clinics
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Downtown Family Clinic",
  "addressJSON": "{\"street\":\"123 Main St\",\"city\":\"Springfield\",\"state\":\"IL\",\"postal\":\"62701\"}"
}

###

### 2-C  GET single clinic
GET {{host}}/Clinics/{{clinicId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 2-D  PUT update clinic
PUT {{host}}/Clinics/{{clinicId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Downtown Family Clinic – Revised",
  "addressJSON": "{\"street\":\"123 Main St\",\"city\":\"Springfield\",\"state\":\"IL\",\"postal\":\"62701\"}",
  "status": "Active"
}

###

### 2-E  GET non-existent clinic – expect 404
GET {{host}}/Clinics/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000099
Accept: application/json

###

### 2-F  DELETE clinic  (run last in this section)
DELETE {{host}}/Clinics/{{clinicId}}

###


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  3. PATIENTS  –  /Patients
###  Prerequisites: @userId must be set (re-create user if deleted above)
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 3-A  GET all patients
GET {{host}}/Patients
Accept: application/json

###

### 3-B  POST create patient  →  copy PatientID into @patientId above
POST {{host}}/Patients
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userID": "{{userId}}",
  "mrn": "MRN-20260001",
  "name": "Bob Martinez",
  "dob": "1985-03-15",
  "gender": "Male",
  "contactInfoJSON": "{\"email\":\"bob@example.com\",\"phone\":\"555-2001\"}",
  "addressJSON": "{\"street\":\"456 Oak Ave\",\"city\":\"Springfield\",\"state\":\"IL\",\"postal\":\"62702\"}",
  "insuranceInfoJSON": "{\"provider\":\"BlueCross\",\"memberId\":\"BC123456\"}"
}

###

### 3-C  GET single patient
GET {{host}}/Patients/{{patientId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 3-D  PUT update patient
PUT {{host}}/Patients/{{patientId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Robert Martinez",
  "dob": "1985-03-15",
  "gender": "Male",
  "contactInfoJSON": "{\"email\":\"robert@example.com\",\"phone\":\"555-2002\"}",
  "addressJSON": "{\"street\":\"456 Oak Ave\",\"city\":\"Springfield\",\"state\":\"IL\",\"postal\":\"62702\"}",
  "insuranceInfoJSON": "{\"provider\":\"BlueCross\",\"memberId\":\"BC123456\"}",
  "consentStatus": "Signed"
}

###

### 3-E  POST validation error – invalid gender
POST {{host}}/Patients
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userID": "{{userId}}",
  "mrn": "MRN-ERR-001",
  "name": "Test Patient",
  "dob": "1990-01-01",
  "gender": "Unknown"
}

###

### 3-F  GET intake forms for patient
GET {{host}}/Patients/{{patientId}}/intake-forms
Accept: application/json

###

### 3-G  POST create intake form for patient
POST {{host}}/Patients/{{patientId}}/intake-forms
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "visitReason": "Annual physical examination",
  "symptomsJSON": "[\"fatigue\",\"mild headache\"]",
  "allergiesJSON": "[\"penicillin\"]",
  "medicationsJSON": "[\"lisinopril 10mg\"]",
  "source": "Portal"
}

###

### 3-H  POST intake form validation error – missing visitReason
POST {{host}}/Patients/{{patientId}}/intake-forms
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "visitReason": "",
  "source": "InvalidSource"
}

###

### 3-I  DELETE patient  (run last in this section)
DELETE {{host}}/Patients/{{patientId}}

###


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  4. SCHEDULING – /Scheduling
###  Sub-resources: providers, appointments, waitlist, rooms
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ── 4a. Providers ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 4a-A  GET all providers
GET {{host}}/Scheduling/providers
Accept: application/json

###

### 4a-B  POST create provider  →  copy ProviderID into @providerId above
###       Prerequisites: @userId and @clinicId must be set
POST {{host}}/Scheduling/providers
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userID": "{{userId}}",
  "specialty": "General Practice",
  "clinicIDsJSON": "[\"{{clinicId}}\"]",
  "availabilityJSON": "{\"monday\":\"09:00-17:00\",\"tuesday\":\"09:00-17:00\"}",
  "maxDailySlots": 20
}

###

### 4a-C  GET single provider
GET {{host}}/Scheduling/providers/{{providerId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 4a-D  PUT update provider
PUT {{host}}/Scheduling/providers/{{providerId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "specialty": "Family Medicine",
  "clinicIDsJSON": "[\"{{clinicId}}\"]",
  "availabilityJSON": "{\"monday\":\"08:00-16:00\",\"wednesday\":\"08:00-16:00\"}",
  "maxDailySlots": 18,
  "status": "Active"
}

###

### 4a-E  PUT provider validation error – invalid status
PUT {{host}}/Scheduling/providers/{{providerId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "specialty": "Family Medicine",
  "maxDailySlots": 18,
  "status": "Retired"
}

###

### 4a-F  DELETE provider  (run last in this sub-section)
DELETE {{host}}/Scheduling/providers/{{providerId}}

###

# ── 4b. Appointments ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 4b-A  GET all appointments
GET {{host}}/Scheduling/appointments
Accept: application/json

###

### 4b-B  POST create appointment  →  copy AppID into @appointmentId above
###       Prerequisites: @patientId, @providerId, @clinicId, @userId must be set
POST {{host}}/Scheduling/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientID": "{{patientId}}",
  "providerID": "{{providerId}}",
  "clinicID": "{{clinicId}}",
  "scheduledAt": "2026-05-10T09:00:00Z",
  "durationMinutes": 30,
  "mode": "InPerson",
  "reason": "Follow-up consultation",
  "createdBy": "{{userId}}"
}

###

### 4b-C  GET single appointment
GET {{host}}/Scheduling/appointments/{{appointmentId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 4b-D  PUT update appointment
PUT {{host}}/Scheduling/appointments/{{appointmentId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "scheduledAt": "2026-05-10T10:00:00Z",
  "durationMinutes": 45,
  "mode": "Telehealth",
  "reason": "Follow-up consultation (rescheduled)",
  "status": "Confirmed"
}

###

### 4b-E  POST appointment validation error – invalid mode
POST {{host}}/Scheduling/appointments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientID": "{{patientId}}",
  "providerID": "{{providerId}}",
  "clinicID": "{{clinicId}}",
  "scheduledAt": "2026-05-10T09:00:00Z",
  "durationMinutes": 30,
  "mode": "WalkIn",
  "reason": "Routine checkup",
  "createdBy": "{{userId}}"
}

###

### 4b-F  DELETE appointment  (run last in this sub-section)
DELETE {{host}}/Scheduling/appointments/{{appointmentId}}

###

# ── 4c. Waitlist ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 4c-A  GET all waitlist entries
GET {{host}}/Scheduling/waitlist
Accept: application/json

###

### 4c-B  POST create waitlist entry  →  copy WaitID into @waitlistId above
###       Prerequisites: @patientId, @providerId must be set
POST {{host}}/Scheduling/waitlist
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientID": "{{patientId}}",
  "providerID": "{{providerId}}",
  "requestedWindowStart": "2026-05-01T08:00:00Z",
  "requestedWindowEnd": "2026-05-15T18:00:00Z"
}

###

### 4c-C  GET single waitlist entry
GET {{host}}/Scheduling/waitlist/{{waitlistId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 4c-D  PUT update waitlist entry
PUT {{host}}/Scheduling/waitlist/{{waitlistId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "requestedWindowStart": "2026-05-05T08:00:00Z",
  "requestedWindowEnd": "2026-05-20T18:00:00Z",
  "status": "Offered"
}

###

### 4c-E  POST waitlist validation error – end before start
POST {{host}}/Scheduling/waitlist
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "patientID": "{{patientId}}",
  "providerID": "{{providerId}}",
  "requestedWindowStart": "2026-05-15T08:00:00Z",
  "requestedWindowEnd": "2026-05-01T18:00:00Z"
}

###

### 4c-F  DELETE waitlist entry  (run last in this sub-section)
DELETE {{host}}/Scheduling/waitlist/{{waitlistId}}

###

# ── 4d. Rooms ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 4d-A  GET all rooms
GET {{host}}/Scheduling/rooms
Accept: application/json

###

### 4d-B  POST create room  →  copy RoomID into @roomId above
###       Prerequisites: @clinicId must be set
POST {{host}}/Scheduling/rooms
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "clinicID": "{{clinicId}}",
  "name": "Exam Room 1",
  "capacity": 2,
  "resourcesJSON": "{\"equipment\":[\"stethoscope\",\"blood pressure cuff\"]}"
}

###

### 4d-C  GET single room
GET {{host}}/Scheduling/rooms/{{roomId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 4d-D  PUT update room
PUT {{host}}/Scheduling/rooms/{{roomId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Exam Room 1 – Updated",
  "capacity": 3,
  "resourcesJSON": "{\"equipment\":[\"stethoscope\",\"blood pressure cuff\",\"ECG machine\"]}",
  "status": "Available"
}

###

### 4d-E  PUT room validation error – invalid status
PUT {{host}}/Scheduling/rooms/{{roomId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Exam Room 1",
  "capacity": 2,
  "status": "Closed"
}

###

### 4d-F  DELETE room  (run last in this sub-section)
DELETE {{host}}/Scheduling/rooms/{{roomId}}

###


### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  5. ENCOUNTERS  –  /api/v1/encounters
###  Prerequisites: @appointmentId, @patientId, @providerId must be set
### ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 5-A  GET all encounters
GET {{host}}/api/v1/encounters
Accept: application/json

###

### 5-B  POST create encounter  →  copy EncounterID into @encounterId above
POST {{host}}/api/v1/encounters
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "appID": "{{appointmentId}}",
  "patientID": "{{patientId}}",
  "providerID": "{{providerId}}",
  "startAt": "2026-05-10T10:00:00Z",
  "visitType": "FollowUp",
  "chiefComplaint": "Patient reports persistent fatigue and mild headaches for two weeks."
}

###

### 5-C  GET single encounter
GET {{host}}/api/v1/encounters/{{encounterId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 5-D  PUT update encounter
PUT {{host}}/api/v1/encounters/{{encounterId}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "endAt": "2026-05-10T10:45:00Z",
  "visitType": "FollowUp",
  "chiefComplaint": "Patient reports persistent fatigue and mild headaches for two weeks.",
  "encounterNoteURI": "https://notes.clinicflow.internal/enc/12345",
  "status": "Completed"
}

###

### 5-E  GET non-existent encounter – expect 404
GET {{host}}/api/v1/encounters/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000099
Accept: application/json

###

# ── 5f. Orders (nested under Encounter) ──────────────────────────────────────

### 5-F  GET orders for encounter
GET {{host}}/api/v1/encounters/{{encounterId}}/orders
Accept: application/json

###

### 5-G  POST create order on encounter
###       Prerequisites: @userId must be a valid user (OrderedBy is a UserID)
POST {{host}}/api/v1/encounters/{{encounterId}}/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderedBy": "{{userId}}",
  "orderType": "LabTest",
  "orderDetailsJSON": "{\"test\":\"CBC\",\"priority\":\"Routine\",\"notes\":\"Fasting required\"}",
  "expectedAt": "2026-05-11T09:00:00Z"
}

###

### 5-H  POST order on non-existent encounter – expect 404
POST {{host}}/api/v1/encounters/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000099/orders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderedBy": "{{userId}}",
  "orderType": "Imaging",
  "orderDetailsJSON": "{\"type\":\"X-Ray\"}",
  "expectedAt": "2026-05-12T09:00:00Z"
}

###

# ── 5i. Referrals (nested under Encounter) ───────────────────────────────────

### 5-I  GET referrals for encounter
GET {{host}}/api/v1/encounters/{{encounterId}}/referrals
Accept: application/json

###

### 5-J  POST create referral on encounter
###       Prerequisites: @providerId, @appointmentId must be set
POST {{host}}/api/v1/encounters/{{encounterId}}/referrals
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromProvider": "{{providerId}}",
  "toProviderInfoJSON": "{\"name\":\"Dr. Specialist\",\"specialty\":\"Neurology\",\"clinic\":\"NeuroCenter\",\"phone\":\"555-9900\"}",
  "appointmentID": "{{appointmentId}}"
}

###

### 5-K  POST referral on non-existent encounter – expect 404
POST {{host}}/api/v1/encounters/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000099/referrals
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fromProvider": "{{providerId}}",
  "toProviderInfoJSON": "{\"name\":\"Dr. Ghost\",\"specialty\":\"Unknown\"}",
  "appointmentID": null
}

###
